# BUG-689 — apps/api/src/services/billing/family.ts

In `formatDateLabel` (lines 153-177 in original), an invalid IANA timezone causes
`Intl.DateTimeFormat` to throw a RangeError. The catch silently falls back to UTC
with no logging. Per CLAUDE.md "Silent recovery without escalation is banned" —
billing renders displaying the wrong day for affected users is invisible.

FIX: (1) Add `createLogger` import at top of file. (2) Replace `catch {}` with
`catch (err)` and emit structured `billing.format_date.timezone_fallback` warn log.

ADD at line 26 (after `import { getFamilyPoolBreakdownSharing } from '../settings';`):
```typescript
import { createLogger } from '../logger';

const logger = createLogger();
```

REPLACE lines 169-176 (the `catch {}` block) with:
```typescript
  } catch (err) {
    // [BUG-689 / L11.F9] Invalid IANA timezone in billing data — `Intl.DateTimeFormat`
    // throws a RangeError for unrecognized zones. Falling back to UTC silently
    // hid bad subscription/profile timezone columns from observability, so cycle
    // dates rendered to the wrong day for affected users with no audit trail.
    // Emit a structured log so on-call can query "how many billing renders fell
    // back to UTC in 24h" — per CLAUDE.md "Silent recovery without escalation
    // is banned" in billing code.
    logger.warn('[billing] invalid timezone fell back to UTC', {
      event: 'billing.format_date.timezone_fallback',
      requestedTimezone: timeZone,
      locale,
      error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),
    });
    return new Intl.DateTimeFormat(locale, {
      timeZone: 'UTC',
      year: 'numeric',
      month: 'long',
      day: 'numeric',
    }).format(date);
  }
```

