# BUG-695 — apps/api/src/services/llm/providers/openai.ts

In `chatStream` (lines 228-251 in original), TWO empty `catch {}` blocks discard
malformed SSE chunks with no log. Corrupt OpenAI responses are invisible to
observability.

FIX: Replace both empty catches with structured `logger.warn` calls. Discard
behavior preserved (one bad chunk should not kill the stream) but now observable.

REPLACE line 232 `} catch {` block (stream_loop) with:
```typescript
                } catch (err) {
                  // [BUG-695 / L11.F15] Previously an empty catch silently
                  // discarded malformed SSE chunks, leaving corrupt LLM
                  // responses invisible. Log structurally so we can query
                  // "openai.sse.malformed count over 24h" — discard still
                  // happens (one bad chunk should not kill the stream) but
                  // it is now observable. Truncate the chunk to avoid
                  // bloating logs with multi-KB payloads.
                  logger.warn('[llm:openai] malformed SSE chunk discarded', {
                    event: 'openai.sse.malformed',
                    site: 'stream_loop',
                    chunk: jsonStr.slice(0, 200),
                    error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),
                  });
                }
```

